Subject: winex11: flush XdndStatus replies before the source's
 next client message

XdndStatus was queued but not flushed, so a fast source (GNOME Files,
Nautilus-based file managers under Xwayland) could send further
XdndPosition messages and a final XdndLeave that overtake the queued
acceptance, making external drags into Live intermittently refuse the
drop. Flush each status reply as it is sent.

Origin: ENCORE (wowitsjack) patches/encore-wine.patch, dlls/winex11.drv/event.c
hunk, reviewed and ported unchanged to this wine-11.11 tree.
---
 dlls/winex11.drv/event.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c b/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c
index 50c56e6f..f48cae38 100644
--- a/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c
+++ b/dlls/winex11.drv/event.c
@@ -1688,6 +1688,9 @@ static void handle_xdnd_position_event( HWND hwnd, XClientMessageEvent *event )
     e.data.l[3] = 0; /* Empty Rect */
     e.data.l[4] = drop_effect_to_xdnd_action( effect );
     XSendEvent( event->display, event->data.l[0], False, NoEventMask, (XEvent *)&e );
+    /* The source may keep sending positions without waiting for a reply.  Flush
+     * each status before a queued XdndLeave can overtake the acceptance. */
+    XFlush( event->display );
 }
 
 
